h3. Problem Definition
JiraHomeHealthCheck doesn't have detailed logging for error path

Code in {{com.atlassian.jira.health.checks.JiraHomeHealthCheck}} will log a message in case of happy flow:
{code:Java|borderStyle=solid}
private final LazyReference<Either<JiraHomeStartupCheckFailure, File>> homeDirRef = new LazyReference<Either<JiraHomeStartupCheckFailure, File>>() {
        @Override
        protected Either<JiraHomeStartupCheckFailure, File> create() throws Exception {
            final Either<JiraHomeStartupCheckFailure, File> result = getConfiguredJiraHome().flatMap(jiraHome -> validateJiraHome(jiraHome));
            result.forEach(homeDir -> log.info("The jira.home directory '" + homeDir.getAbsolutePath() + "' is validated and locked for exclusive use by this instance."));
            return result;
        }
{code}

Eg.
{noformat}
2020-01-13 17:08:12,779+0100 localhost-startStop-1 INFO      [c.a.jira.startup.JiraHomeStartupCheck] The jira.home directory '/work/app/jira/application-data/jira_8.5' is validated and locked for exclusive use by this instance.
2020-01-13 17:08:12,937+0100 JIRA-Bootstrap INFO      [c.a.jira.startup.JiraStartupLogger] ...
2020-01-13 17:08:13,400+0100 JIRA-Bootstrap INFO      [c.a.j.config.database.SystemDatabaseConfigurationLoader] Reading database configuration from /work/app/jira/application-data/jira_8.5/dbconfig.xml
2020-01-13 17:08:13,783+0100 JIRA-Bootstrap INFO      [c.a.jira.startup.JiraStartupLogger] Running JIRA startup checks.
{noformat}

At the same time, there is not much logging in case of error path:
{noformat}
2020-07-28 16:34:37,723 JIRA-Bootstrap INFO      [c.a.j.config.database.SystemDatabaseConfigurationLoader] Reading database configuration from /appl/jira/home/dbconfig.xml
2020-07-28 16:34:37,899 JIRA-Bootstrap INFO      [c.a.jira.startup.JiraStartupLogger] Running JIRA startup checks.
2020-07-28 16:34:37,899 JIRA-Bootstrap FATAL      [c.a.jira.startup.JiraStartupLogger] Startup check failed. JIRA will be locked.
{noformat}

h3. Suggested Solution
Add additional logging

h3. Note
For the reference, validation checks done by JiraHomeHealthCheck:
{code:Java|borderStyle=solid}
   // Validate the jira.home, and create the directory if required
    // Note that we only save jiraHomeDirectory if everything is valid.
    private Either<JiraHomeStartupCheckFailure, File> validateJiraHome(final String jiraHome) {
        final File proposedJiraHome = new File(jiraHome);
        return checkProposedHomeAbsolute(proposedJiraHome, jiraHome)
                .flatMap(this::checkWebappPathCollision)
                .flatMap(this::checkJiraHomeCreationIsPossible)
                .flatMap(this::createJiraHomeAndSharedHome)
                .flatMap(this::lockJiraHome);
    }
{code}


h3.Workaround
None

h3. Problem Definition
Current Label's cache (CachingLabelStore) has a limited size and short TTL, for large number of labels this might be inefficient. 
* com.atlassian.jira.issue.label.CachingLabelStore
{code:Java|borderStyle=solid}
   public CachingLabelStore(final OfBizLabelStore delegateStore, final CacheManager cacheManager) {
        this.delegateStore = delegateStore;
        cache = cacheManager.getCache(getClass().getName() + ".cache",
                this::loadCacheLabels,
                new CacheSettingsBuilder().expireAfterAccess(10, TimeUnit.MINUTES).maxEntries(1000).build());
    }
{code}
* cache key
{code:Java|borderStyle=solid}
 public Set<Label> getLabels(final Long issueId, final Long customFieldId) {
        final CacheKey key = new CacheKey(issueId, customFieldId);
        return cache.get(key);
    }
{code}

h3. Suggested Solution
* Increase the cache limit
* Increase TTL  

h3. Workaround 
None

